</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em          Am         Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. Eli, Eli, lamma sabactani
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am              Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Why is your salvation so far from my groaning,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   by day I call, and you don’t answer
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                  Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   by night, there is no rest for me.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   But you are the Holy One,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   you who live in the praises of my people.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   In you my fathers hoped,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in you they trusted and you rescued them;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to you they cried out and you saved them,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                            Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in you they hoped and they were never confounded.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Yet here I am? Why don’t you help me?
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                Em                 B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Is it perhaps that I’m not a man? This I am, a worm!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Scorn of mankind! Jest of the people!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Everyone who sees me, laughs at me,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   they sneer and shake their heads and say:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   “He trusted in God, let Him deliver him
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   if he says that He loves him so much.”
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Yes, you love me; yes, you do love me!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   You drew me out of my mother’s womb.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   When she gave birth, you took me up,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   since from my mother’s womb you have been my God,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                        Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   when I was born, she entrusted me to you.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em          Am         Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. Eli, Eli, lamma sabactani
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am              Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Do not be far from me,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   trouble is near, no one helps me!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">     B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   A herd of bulls surrounds me.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   bulls of Bashan close in on me.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Their jaws are agape for me
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   like lions tearing and roaring.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   I am dirty water that is thrown out,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   all my bones are out of joint.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   My heart is like wax, melting inside me,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   my palate is as dry as a tile,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and my tongue is stuck to my throat,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                         Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and you leave me lying in the dust of death.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em          Am         Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. Eli, Eli, lamma sabactani
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am              Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Countless dogs surround me,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   a band of evil-doers encircles me;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   they tie my hands and my feet,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   I can count all my bones.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   They stare at me, they gaze at me:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   they divide my clothes,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                        Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   they draw lots on my tunic.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                       Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   But you, my God don’t stay far from me,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                             Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   my strength, my strength, come quickly to help me.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Deliver me from the sword,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   my life from the claws of the dogs,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   save me, save me from the mouth,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   from the mouth of the lions
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and from the horns of the bulls.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Em          Am         Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. Eli, Eli, lamma sabactani
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   Am              Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   C                                   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. I will proclaim your name to the brothers,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   C                                       B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   I will praise you in the midst of the assembly
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and say:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am                      B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   You who fear the Lord, praise Him!
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               Am              B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   People of Jacob glorify the Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   let the race of Israel give Him glory;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                         Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   for He was not disgusted by this poor man,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                                Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He’s the only one who was not scandalized of me
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He did not despise this wretched man,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He didn’t hide His face from him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   but at his cry for help, He answered him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   at his cry He listened to him;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   now I know that the poor will be satisfied,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   those who search you will find you
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   that their hearts, their hearts will live,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   will live eternally, will live forever.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   C                                            B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   All the ends of the earth will return to the Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   all the peoples will bow down before him.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Because the kingdom, the kingdom belongs to the Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                         Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He rules over all the nations.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   All those who sleep under the earth will bow down
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   before Him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                                Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to Him will bow all those who go down to the dust.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   For I, will live, I will live for Him,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                        Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   my descendants shall serve Him.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   B7
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   They will proclaim the Lord to the generation
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   still to come;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   they will announce to them what He has done for me;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to the people yet to be born they will say:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   “Behold the work of the Lord!”

